Reasoning: The paper presents a novel knowledge domain visualization of educational technology based on readership patterns in an online reference management system. This involves analyzing and visualizing large amounts of data, which falls under the scope of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to analyze the data, which falls under the scope of deep learning (cs.DL). Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also relevant as the paper discusses the analysis of co-readership patterns. Finally, the paper touches on the social and ethical implications of educational technology, which could fall under the scope of cybersecurity (cs.CY).
